  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nAfter some time (days) the state sync stalls and log is full of these:\r\n\r\n```\r\nDEBUG  11-18 20:55:36       StateDownloader  Task failure traceback\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/p2p/service.py\", line 141, in _run_task_wrapper\r\n    await awaitable\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/trinity/sync/full/state.py\", line 218, in _request_and_process_nodes\r\n    await self._process_nodes(node_data)\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/trinity/sync/full/state.py\", line 134, in _process_nodes\r\n    await self.scheduler.process([(node_key, node)])\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/trinity/sync/full/hexary_trie.py\", line 227, in process\r\n    await self.commit(request)\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/trinity/sync/full/hexary_trie.py\", line 237, in commit\r\n    self.nodes_cache[request.node_key] = b''\r\n  File \"/home/ubuntu/py-evm/eth/db/backends/level.py\", line 51, in __setitem__\r\n    self.db.put(key, value)\r\n  File \"plyvel/_plyvel.pyx\", line 331, in plyvel._plyvel.DB.put\r\n  File \"plyvel/_plyvel.pyx\", line 88, in plyvel._plyvel.raise_for_status\r\nplyvel._plyvel.IOError: b'IO error: /tmp/pyevm-state-sync-cachehygvcf44/006748.ldb: Too many open files'\r\n WARNING  11-18 20:55:36       StateDownloader  Task <coroutine object StateDownloader._request_and_process_nodes at 0x7f9011ec6b48> finished unexpectedly: b'IO error: /tmp/pyevm-state-sync-cachehygvcf44/006748.ldb: Too many open files'\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis was reported before: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/issues/524\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\n:see_no_evil: :hear_no_evil: \r\n",
