    "body": "Correct! I just looked briefly into this (because it's the end of my working day) but if anyone wants to take a stab at it, Here's what I believe geth does:\r\n\r\n1. Figure out the max open file supported by the OS per process\r\n\r\n2. Reserve half of them for LevelDB https://github.com/holiman/go-ethereum/blob/ec28a58cc1cc1671a09061d5aa24d1c4c9c77b9f/cmd/utils/flags.go#L716-L730\r\n\r\n3. Pass that to level db on init https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/d31f1f4fdb905acb3d7c766683e584bb17f8df0d/ethdb/database.go#L77\r\n\r\nNotice that `OpenFilesCacheCapacity` is essentially  `MaxOpenFiles`\r\n\r\nhttps://gitter.im/ethereum/go-ethereum?at=5547e9e1dfe856bc1179d8c7\r\n\r\n",
